&lt;p>A three-layer hierarchical memory system for embodied agents built on &lt;strong>Gated DeltaNet (GDN)&lt;/strong> fast-weight matrices, integrated into the Genie Envisioner Slow-Fast VLA architecture.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Architecture:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Layer 1 (Physical)&lt;/strong> — TTT layer inside each of the 28 DiT blocks of GE-Base (2B), inserted after cross-attention, before FFN. Shared W ∈ ℝ^{64×64} updated at 5 Hz Slow Path.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Layer 2–3 (Object / Behavioral)&lt;/strong> — External to Slow Path. CLIP/DINO detects objects from visual latents, writes W_obj and W_person via online GDN updates. Memory tokens injected into GE-Act (160M, 30 Hz) via cross-attention.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Key properties:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Constant 256 KB memory regardless of episode length&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&amp;lt;1ms GDN update latency (SRAM fast-weight computation)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>3D RoPE spatial encoding for object-position binding&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Dual CUDA stream + Double Buffering scheduling&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Target:&lt;/strong> ICRA / CoRL 2026 | Affiliations: Tongji CS × PKU DLIB × 智元机器人&lt;/p>
